<div class="page">

  <h2>Rules & Regulations</h2>
  <div class="subtitle">
    Applicable for Free Auditions & Advanced Rounds
  </div>

  <div class="rule-section">
    <h3>1. Competition Structure</h3>
    <p>Rhythm Rise is conducted in multiple stages including Free Auditions, District Finals, and further advanced rounds.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="rule-section">
    <h3>2. Performance Duration</h3>
    <p><strong>Auditions (Free – Short Format)</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Dance: Maximum 2 minutes</li>
      <li>Singing: Maximum 1 minute 30 seconds</li>
      <li>Judges may stop a performance once sufficient evaluation is completed</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>District Finals</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Solo Dance: Maximum 3 minutes</li>
      <li>Classical & Group Dance: Maximum 4 minutes</li>
      <li>Singing: Maximum 3 minutes</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="rule-section">
    <h3>3. Music & Genre</h3>
    <p>Participants must select music matching their chosen category. Vulgar or inappropriate content is strictly prohibited.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="rule-section">
    <h3>4. Costumes & Makeup</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Auditions: Costumes and makeup are optional</li>
      <li>Finals: Costumes and makeup are mandatory</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="rule-section">
    <h3>5. Selection & Registration</h3>
    <p>Selection is based solely on judges’ evaluation. Participation in advanced rounds is optional and may involve a registration fee communicated after selection.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="rule-section">
    <h3>6. Judges’ Decision</h3>
    <p>Judges’ decisions are final and binding. Rhythm Rise Management Committee holds final authority.</p>
  </div>

</div>

<footer>
